************************************************************************
*                                                                      *
*      Simulate imino 2D spectra using chemical shift predictors.      *
*      Only support prediction for RNA groups within A-form helix.     *
*                                                                      *
************************************************************************

************************************************************************
Follow steps below to simulate imino spectrum
1. Update the input file, e.g. <tP5abc.seq>. Please provide the secondary
   structure in bracket-dot line. Note that this tool only supports canonical 
   base pairs (Watson-Crick and GU wobble).
2. Run genimino.py to generate the predicted imino chemical shift table.
   The script will give a demonstration.
3. Under `sim.imino` folder, run clean.sh and then, run mkucsf.py to create a
   simulated imino 2D spectrum.

